-- Suncor Oil-Sands Production, Syncrude Output Rise in August
-- B y   L y n n   D o a n
-- 2012-09-04T23:27:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/suncor-oil-sands-production-syncrude-output-rise-in-august-1-.html
Suncor Energy Inc. (SU) ’s oil-sands
production increased 6.3 percent to 373,000 barrels a day in
August from a month earlier.  Last month’s output, which includes upgraded sweet and sour
synthetic crude oil and diesel and non-upgraded bitumen, was up
from 351,000 in July, Calgary-based Suncor said on its  website .
The year-to-date average is 321,000.  Suncor was scheduled to perform maintenance on its No. 2
upgrader in  Alberta  beginning at the end of the third quarter
and lasting into the fourth. Work will also be done at a mining
extraction site and the MacKay River central processing plant
during the turnaround, the company said in a filing July 25.  Syncrude production averaged 359,500 barrels a day in
August, up from 262,000 in July,  Canadian Oil Sands (COS)  said on its
 website . Canadian Oil Sands is the largest owner in the Syncrude
Canada Ltd. venture.  To contact the reporter on this story:
